article.description: Stevie Jordan scored 22 points and Kahlil Thomas 17, including a free throw with 21 seconds remaining in overtime to seal a 93-90 comeback win at Monmouth on Saturday.
article.headline: Rider knocks off Monmouth 93-90 in OT to share MAAC lead
article.linkText: Rider knocks off Monmouth 93-90 in OT to share MAAC lead
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Stevie Jordan scored 22 points and Kahlil Thomas 17, including a free throw with 21 seconds remaining in overtime to seal a 93-90 comeback win at Monmouth on Saturday. The Broncs (9-5, 2-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic) outscored Monmouth 12-7 over the last three minutes of overtime to claim the late lead and the win. Monmouth (10-5, 2-1), with its first MAAC loss, falls into an early tie for the conference lead with Rider and Iona. Jordan, a freshman, shot 7-for-11 from the field with three 3-pointers and six assists. Thomas and Jimmie Taylor added 17 points each. Thomas also grabbed 13 rebounds- 11 off the defensive boards -- for his fifth double-double this season. Justin Robinson led Monmouth with 28 points and seven assists and Micah Seaborn scored 17 but each missed a 3-point try in the final 11 seconds.
